        {
          "id": "R_TO_KIOSK_MENU",
          "type": "redirect",
          "target": "N_KIOSK_MENU"
        },
        {
          "id": "N_KIOSK_INTRO",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "The kiosk screen is touch-sensitive in the way old glass pretends to be.\nA header reads: SPINDLE ADMIN SERVICES \u2014 LOBBY ACCESS.\n\nWELCOME.\nSELECT A SERVICE CATEGORY.\nUNAUTHORIZED USE IS SUBJECT TO REVIEW.",
          "next": "N_KIOSK_MENU"
        },
        {
          "id": "N_KIOSK_MENU",
          "type": "player_choice",
          "speakerId": "PLAYER",
          "choices": [
            {
              "id": "USE_DIR",
              "text": "use \"Select: Directory.\"",
              "next": "N_KIOSK_DIR"
            },
            {
              "id": "USE_WORK",
              "text": "use \"Select: Work Orders.\"",
              "next": "N_KIOSK_WORK"
            },
            {
              "id": "USE_INCIDENT",
              "text": "use \"Select: Incident / Safety.\"",
              "next": "N_KIOSK_INCIDENT"
            },
            {
              "id": "SHOW_OLEA",
              "text": "show \"Show OLEA credentials to the kiosk.\"",
              "conditions": [
                {
                  "key": "player.factions",
                  "op": "in",
                  "value": [
                    "OLEA"
                  ]
                }
              ],
              "next": "N_KIOSK_SHOW"
            },
            {
              "id": "LOOK_STEPBACK",
              "text": "look \"Step back.\"",
              "next": "R_TO_PROMPT"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "N_KIOSK_DIR",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "DIRECTORY ACCESS IS LIMITED IN LOBBY MODE.\nSEARCH RETURNS TITLES ONLY.\nNAMES REQUIRE AUTHENTICATION.\n\nYou try a simple keyword.\n\nRESULTS:\n\u2014 RECEPTION (UNSTAFFED)\n\u2014 RECEPTION OVERSIGHT (TEMPORARY)\n\u2014 RECEPTION \u2014 AFTER HOURS PROTOCOL\n\nSelecting a result requires authentication.\nIt won\u2019t give names. It will give vocabulary.",
          "next": "R_TO_KIOSK_MENU"
        },
        {
          "id": "N_KIOSK_WORK",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "WORK ORDER SUBMISSION REQUIRES A SPONSOR ID.\nLOBBY MODE MAY PRINT STANDARD FORMS.\nSELECT: PRINT / CANCEL.",
          "next": "N_KIOSK_WORK_CHOICE"
        },
        {
          "id": "N_KIOSK_WORK_CHOICE",
          "type": "player_choice",
          "speakerId": "PLAYER",
          "choices": [
            {
              "id": "USE_PRINT_HEADER",
              "text": "use \"Print standard form header.\"",
              "next": "N_KIOSK_PRINT_HEADER"
            },
            {
              "id": "LOOK_CANCEL",
              "text": "look \"Cancel.\"",
              "next": "R_TO_KIOSK_MENU"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "N_KIOSK_PRINT_HEADER",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "PRINTING: OLEA LEGACY ENERGY ASSETS \u2014 SPINDLE SITE\nFORM HEADER ONLY. NO ROUTING NUMBER ISSUED.\n\nA page feeds out: official letterhead, a site identifier line, and blank fields waiting to be lied into.",
          "next": "R_TO_KIOSK_MENU"
        },
        {
          "id": "N_KIOSK_INCIDENT",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "TO REPORT A SAFETY CONDITION: LIFT HANDSET AT RECEPTION DESK.\nIF NO HANDSET IS PRESENT, COMPLETE FORM S-14 \u201cCONDITION NOTICE.\u201d\nDO NOT USE EMERGENCY CODES IN LOBBY MODE.\n\nLOBBY MODE IS NOT A CONTROL ENVIRONMENT.\n\u201cEMERGENCY\u201d IMPLIES AUTHORITY.\nAUTHORITY MUST BE VERIFIED.",
          "next": "R_TO_KIOSK_MENU"
        },
        {
          "id": "N_KIOSK_SHOW",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "CREDENTIAL PRESENTED.\nCREDENTIAL NOT VERIFIED.\nLIMITATION ADJUSTED: LIMITED LOBBY MODE ENABLED.\nYOU MAY:\n\u2014 PRINT STANDARD HEADERS\n\u2014 VIEW TITLES AND EXTENSIONS\n\u2014 INITIATE A CALL REQUEST\n\nIt doesn\u2019t let you in. It does teach you what \u201cin\u201d is supposed to look like.",
          "next": "R_TO_KIOSK_MENU"
        },
        {
          "id": "R_TO_PHONE_MENU",
          "type": "redirect",
          "target": "N_PHONE_MENU"
        },
        {
          "id": "N_PHONE_INTRO",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "The wall list is laminated over older laminated paper.\nSomeone updated it by adding a sticker that has started to peel, like it\u2019s trying to exit the organization.\n\nExtensions. Departments. Titles that sound like they were invented to move blame around.",
          "next": "N_PHONE_MENU"
        },
        {
          "id": "N_PHONE_MENU",
          "type": "player_choice",
          "speakerId": "PLAYER",
          "choices": [
            {
              "id": "LOOK_TOP",
              "text": "look \"Scan from the top.\"",
              "next": "N_PHONE_TOP"
            },
            {
              "id": "LOOK_OVERSIGHT",
              "text": "look \"Look for 'Oversight' roles.\"",
              "next": "N_PHONE_OVERSIGHT"
            },
            {
              "id": "LOOK_AFTERHOURS",
              "text": "look \"Look for after-hours instructions.\"",
              "next": "N_PHONE_AFTERHOURS"
            },
            {
              "id": "LOOK_STEPBACK",
              "text": "look \"Step back.\"",
              "next": "R_TO_PROMPT"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "N_PHONE_TOP",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "You pick up the rhythm: short numbers for operations, longer for compliance, and a separate block labeled EXTERNAL LIAISONS as if the building is ashamed of them.",
          "next": "R_TO_PHONE_MENU"
        },
        {
          "id": "N_PHONE_OVERSIGHT",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "The list offers safe-sounding titles: Temporary Oversight, Records Custodian (Acting), Facilities Liaison.\nNone of them promise presence. All of them promise deniability.",
          "next": "R_TO_PHONE_MENU"
        },
        {
          "id": "N_PHONE_AFTERHOURS",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "A boxed note: AFTER HOURS: DO NOT CONTACT SECURITY FOR ADMIN MATTERS.\nUnder it, smaller: SECURITY WILL CONTACT YOU IF NECESSARY.\nIt reads like a threat that was formatted by committee.",
          "next": "R_TO_PHONE_MENU"
        },
        {
          "id": "R_TO_PLAQUE_MENU",
          "type": "redirect",
          "target": "N_PLAQUE_MENU"
        },
        {
          "id": "N_PLAQUE_INTRO",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "The plaque is bolted to the wall like it\u2019s holding the building\u2019s identity in place.\nA corner is scuffed clean where someone\u2019s hand must have worried it, again and again.\n\nThe text is bureaucratic, not commemorative\u2014meant to outlast argument.",
          "next": "N_PLAQUE_MENU"
        },
        {
          "id": "N_PLAQUE_MENU",
          "type": "player_choice",
          "speakerId": "PLAYER",
          "choices": [
            {
              "id": "LOOK_DESIGNATION",
              "text": "look \"Read the designation line.\"",
              "next": "N_PLAQUE_DESIGNATION"
            },
            {
              "id": "LOOK_OWNERSHIP",
              "text": "look \"Read the ownership / agency line.\"",
              "next": "N_PLAQUE_OWNERSHIP"
            },
            {
              "id": "LOOK_TAG",
              "text": "look \"Look for an asset tag.\"",
              "next": "N_PLAQUE_TAG"
            },
            {
              "id": "LOOK_STEPBACK",
              "text": "look \"Step back.\"",
              "next": "R_TO_PROMPT"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "N_PLAQUE_DESIGNATION",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "S.P.I.N.D.L.E. \u2014 Spatial Power Inertial Node for Distributed Load Equalization.\nThe acronym is confident. The expansion is defensive.",
          "next": "R_TO_PLAQUE_MENU"
        },
        {
          "id": "N_PLAQUE_OWNERSHIP",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "An ownership chain rendered in tiny stamped text: municipal authority, then OLEA stewardship language, then a clause about \u201ccontinued operation pending retirement.\u201d\nIt\u2019s written like closure is a moral act.",
          "next": "R_TO_PLAQUE_MENU"
        },
        {
          "id": "N_PLAQUE_TAG",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "An asset ID is present, partially abraded, but still legible enough to cite.\nNext to it: a seal that implies someone once checked a box and thereby made the machine real.",
          "next": "R_TO_PLAQUE_MENU"
        },
        {
          "id": "R_TO_DRAWERS_MENU",
          "type": "redirect",
          "target": "N_DRAWERS_MENU"
        },
        {
          "id": "N_DRAWERS_INTRO",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "The reception desk drawers resist at first, then slide like they\u2019ve been waiting to be asked properly.\nThe smell is paper, toner, and a faint sting of old adhesive.",
          "next": "N_DRAWERS_MENU"
        },
        {
          "id": "N_DRAWERS_MENU",
          "type": "player_choice",
          "speakerId": "PLAYER",
          "choices": [
            {
              "id": "USE_TOP",
              "text": "use \"Open the top drawer.\"",
              "next": "N_DRAWERS_TOP"
            },
            {
              "id": "USE_BOTTOM",
              "text": "use \"Open the bottom drawer.\"",
              "next": "N_DRAWERS_BOTTOM_1"
            },
            {
              "id": "LOOK_STEPBACK",
              "text": "look \"Step back.\"",
              "next": "R_TO_PROMPT"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "N_DRAWERS_TOP",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "Forms. Carbon copies. A roll of VISITOR stickers that says TEMPORARY in cheerful red.\nA stamp pad so dry it feels like negligence.\n\nNot signed. Pre-signed\u2014worse. A stack of letterhead with a printed name block and no signature, meant to be \u201cefficient.\u201d",
          "next": "R_TO_DRAWERS_MENU"
        },
        {
          "id": "N_DRAWERS_BOTTOM_1",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "Old binders with tabs: ACCESS, ROUTING, INCIDENT.\nAnd a small metal stamp: RECEIVED \u2014 ADMIN LOBBY.\nSomeone cared very deeply about when paper entered a room.",
          "next": "N_DRAWERS_BOTTOM_PLAYER"
        },
        {
          "id": "N_DRAWERS_BOTTOM_PLAYER",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "PLAYER",
          "text": "Take it.",
          "next": "N_DRAWERS_BOTTOM_2"
        },
        {
          "id": "N_DRAWERS_BOTTOM_2",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "You pocket the stamp and a few blank headers.\nIt\u2019s not authority. It\u2019s the costume authority wears.",
          "next": "R_TO_DRAWERS_MENU"
        },
        {
          "id": "N_COMPILE_1",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "You stand where the camera over the kiosk would have had the best view, back when anyone pretended to monitor it.\nBetween the plaque\u2019s wording, the phone list\u2019s titles, and the kiosk\u2019s \u201climited\u201d print options, you have enough to sound inevitable.",
          "next": "N_COMPILE_2"
        },
        {
          "id": "N_COMPILE_2",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "PLAYER",
          "text": "Identifiers. Points of contact. Letterhead.",
          "next": "N_COMPILE_3"
        },
        {
          "id": "N_COMPILE_3",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "You note the kiosk\u2019s limitations, the extension structure, and the asset designation\u2014three different kinds of legitimacy, all mutually incompatible.\nThey will still work on the same people.",
          "next": "END_COMPILE"
        },
        {
          "id": "END_COMPILE",
          "type": "end",
          "outcomeId": "lobby_kiosk_observed",
          "effects": [
            {
              "key": "knowledge.lobbyKioskLimited",
              "action": "set",
              "value": true
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}
